1
00:00:04,160 --> 00:00:07,084
In our position

2
00:00:07,084 --> 00:00:12,934
direct contact with Kṛṣṇa
yields little substance.

3
00:00:13,214 --> 00:00:16,264
[Deep Krishna Connection]

4
00:00:16,484 --> 00:00:20,774
In the case 
of actual exalted devotees

5
00:00:21,288 --> 00:00:27,175
the most indirect contact
yields the highest substance.

6
00:00:28,392 --> 00:00:33,612
So, if Śrīmatī Rādhārāṇī
sees a tree, a tamal tree …

7
00:00:34,327 --> 00:00:40,067
maybe a very deep 
Kṛṣṇa connection.

8
00:00:40,575 --> 00:00:42,953
We hear about 
the Vedic science

9
00:00:42,953 --> 00:00:48,453
of auspicious 
and inauspicious signs.

10
00:00:48,595 --> 00:00:50,690
Like if you’re going travelling,

11
00:00:50,690 --> 00:00:52,942
if someone goes 
by carrying empty buckets—

12
00:00:52,942 --> 00:00:54,218
inauspicious.

13
00:00:54,218 --> 00:00:55,654
If those buckets 
are full of something—

14
00:00:55,654 --> 00:00:57,196
auspicious.

15
00:00:57,206 --> 00:01:00,085
And there are
many other things.

16
00:01:01,305 --> 00:01:02,679
So, we are told,
they indicate, “Oh!
 

17
00:01:02,679 --> 00:01:06,253
Now it’s a good time to travel.”
“Oh, no! Not to travel.”

18
00:01:06,253 --> 00:01:09,011
When we were 
with Mr. Shau,

19
00:01:09,011 --> 00:01:11,077
Avadhūt Mahārāj
and I in Puri,

20
00:01:11,077 --> 00:01:13,797
we were in some place 
and were about to go to do something,

21
00:01:13,797 --> 00:01:15,378
and someone sneezed.

22
00:01:15,378 --> 00:01:16,849
Mr. Shau said,
“We have to wait.”

23
00:01:16,849 --> 00:01:19,439
[Laughing]

24
00:01:19,649 --> 00:01:21,198
But what’s interesting,

25
00:01:21,198 --> 00:01:25,453
Chakravartī Ṭhākur will say,
“This science,
 

26
00:01:25,453 --> 00:01:29,444
we can trace this science back
to Śrīmatī Rādhārāṇī Herself.

27
00:01:29,444 --> 00:01:34,666
But She observes 
all these different signs

28
00:01:34,666 --> 00:01:38,640
as indicative of whether
or not meeting …

29
00:01:38,640 --> 00:01:43,460
it’s favorable
to meet with Kṛṣṇa.”

30
00:01:45,218 --> 00:01:48,313
That’s the value
of this science.

31
00:01:49,613 --> 00:01:55,094
So, Guru Mahārāj 
will say,

32
00:01:55,114 --> 00:01:58,072
(when it comes to interpretation
or how we see anything)

33
00:01:58,072 --> 00:02:01,718
“Depends on where 
we take our stand.”

34
00:02:01,718 --> 00:02:05,567
So, if we take a stand 
in the nirguṇa-plane,

35
00:02:05,567 --> 00:02:08,145
which is where
Śukadeva begins from,

36
00:02:08,145 --> 00:02:11,909
then we’ll see things
from a certain perspective.

37
00:02:11,909 --> 00:02:13,490
And there’s gradation
in everywhere and everything,

38
00:02:13,490 --> 00:02:16,596
so we go deep 
into the nirguṇa-plane.

39
00:02:16,596 --> 00:02:20,135
That means we have

40
00:02:20,135 --> 00:02:24,074
the objective world,
subjective world,

41
00:02:24,074 --> 00:02:29,288
super subjective world and
the super-super subjective world,

42
00:02:29,288 --> 00:02:33,100
means Goloka,
the aprākṛta-līlā of Kṛṣṇa,

43
00:02:33,100 --> 00:02:37,014
where everything is perfect
and will be interpreted

44
00:02:37,014 --> 00:02:41,059
in terms of the Absolute,

45
00:02:41,059 --> 00:02:44,310
a highest interest
of the Supreme Absolute.

46
00:02:44,350 --> 00:02:50,665
As Guru Mahārāj said 
how to show Subal and Śrīdām:

47
00:02:50,665 --> 00:02:55,217
“Ready to fulfill
the inner desires of Kṛṣṇa.”

48
00:02:56,074 --> 00:02:57,712
There’s that plane.

49
00:02:57,712 --> 00:03:01,282
Then here, in this world,
basically we are operating

50
00:03:01,282 --> 00:03:04,592
in terms 
of the intermediate position,

51
00:03:04,592 --> 00:03:06,311
madhyama-adhikārī,
distinguishing,

52
00:03:06,311 --> 00:03:08,743
“Well, this is good,
that’s not good;

53
00:03:08,743 --> 00:03:11,712
this is desirable,
that’s undesirable.”

54
00:03:11,712 --> 00:03:15,077
Some discrimination 
is being applied.

55
00:03:15,077 --> 00:03:19,605
But from a higher perspective
everything is moving perfectly,

56
00:03:19,605 --> 00:03:24,105
according to the sweet will

57
00:03:24,105 --> 00:03:27,727
or the will 
of the Sweet Absolute.

58
00:03:30,107 --> 00:03:32,443
Guru Mahārāj would say,
“We have to prepare

59
00:03:32,453 --> 00:03:36,629
to surrender ourselves
to a whimsical Lord.

60
00:03:38,621 --> 00:03:43,279
In this world we don’t want 
to be subject to someone’s whims,

61
00:03:43,427 --> 00:03:46,256
but when you are dealing 
with the Absolute

62
00:03:46,256 --> 00:03:48,623
why the hesitation?

63
00:03:48,623 --> 00:03:52,210
He’s the Absolute,
ultimate and absolute good.

64
00:03:52,210 --> 00:03:57,740
His whims are 
for the eternal benefit

65
00:03:57,740 --> 00:04:00,990
of everyone and everything.

